HEADWORD: Capitibranchiata
<hw>Cap`i*ti*bran`chi*a"ta</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n. pl.</pos>
<ety>[NL., from L. <ets>caput</ets>, <ets>capitis</ets>, head +
<ets>-branchiae</ets> gills.]</ety> <fld>(Zool.)</fld> <def>A division
of annelids in which the gills arise from or near the head. See
<er>Tubicola</er>.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

